OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FGovernment immigration plan
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fsuffers House of Lords     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fdefeat                     
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The government has suffered a defeat in
OL,6, the House of Lords over its plans to   
OL,7, change immigration law.                
OL,9,FThe Nationality and Borders Bill would 
OL,10,Fallow the UK authorities to strip      
OL,11,Fsomeone of their British citizenship   
OL,12,Fwithout warning.                       
OL,14,FBut crossbench peer Baroness D'Souza,  
OL,15,Fwho argued this would be "unjust",     
OL,16,Fsubmitted an amendment which was passed
OL,17,Fby a majority of 44 votes.             
OL,19,FThe bill will now go back to the House 
OL,20,Fof Commons, which backs the government.
